==English==

===Etymology===
From {{L.}} [[melior]] ''better'' +[[-ism]]. Reportedly coined by British author [[w:George Eliot|George Eliot]] in her letters, published in 1877.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The view or [[doctrine]] that the [[world]] is neither entirely [[bad]] nor entirely [[good]], and can be [[improve]]d through human [[effort]].  Understood as an [[intermediate]] outlook, between [[optimism]] and [[pessimism]].

